WEBVTT

1
00:01:43.001 --> 00:01:44.468
Oh my god!

2
00:01:45.502 --> 00:01:47.971
Did you sleep here?

3
00:01:51.375 --> 00:01:52.595
Sorry.

4
00:01:52.595 --> 00:01:55.245
Stop drinking with college students
until dawn.

5
00:01:55.245 --> 00:01:56.736
You're already over thirty, right?

6
00:01:56.736 --> 00:01:58.782
Mature at once.

7
00:01:58.782 --> 00:02:00.236
Where is?

8
00:02:00.236 --> 00:02:02.285
Did you see a red USB around here?

9
00:02:02.786 --> 00:02:03.687
Sorry?

10
00:02:03.687 --> 00:02:05.334
My red USB.

11
00:02:05.334 --> 00:02:06.323
Well...

12
00:02:06.323 --> 00:02:08.392
I'm in a hurry.

13
00:02:08.392 --> 00:02:09.859
Look it up, okay?

14
00:02:09.859 --> 00:02:11.328
Immediately.

15
00:02:11.328 --> 00:02:14.198
When you have time, clean this pigsty.

16
00:02:14.198 --> 00:02:16.468
This is a disaster.

17
00:02:16.468 --> 00:02:19.636
Don't you think it's time
to put order in your life?

18
00:02:21.275 --> 00:02:23.140
Teacher.

19
00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:24.374
Yeah?

20
00:02:27.035 --> 00:02:29.846
Do you remember what you told me a while ago?

21
00:02:31.155 --> 00:02:32.816
That? What did I say?

22
00:02:35.323 --> 00:02:37.954
He asked me if I cared about my future.

23
00:02:38.422 --> 00:02:41.024
He said I was sabotaging my own life.

24
00:02:44.670 --> 00:02:46.096
Did I say that?

25
00:02:46.096 --> 00:02:48.532
I was quite rude, sorry.

26
00:02:48.532 --> 00:02:50.200
Professor, I...

27
00:02:52.334 --> 00:02:55.372
I won't hurt myself anymore.

28
00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:58.042
I started to take charge

29
00:02:58.042 --> 00:02:59.576
of my life.

30
00:03:31.709 --> 00:03:33.176
Hello.

31
00:03:34.178 --> 00:03:35.946
Me, as always.

32
00:03:35.946 --> 00:03:37.614
And how are you?

33
00:03:39.242 --> 00:03:40.450
That?

34
00:03:42.177 --> 00:03:43.801
I feel very good,

35
00:03:43.801 --> 00:03:46.056
but the doctors insist that it is cancer.

36
00:03:46.824 --> 00:03:49.142
But you look healthy.

37
00:03:49.142 --> 00:03:51.122
Exact.

38
00:03:51.122 --> 00:03:53.364
What you don't know can't hurt you.

39
00:03:53.364 --> 00:03:55.578
Knowing is the real disease.

40
00:03:55.578 --> 00:03:56.466
Hey.

41
00:03:56.466 --> 00:03:59.658
And I don't think it's unfair.

42
00:03:59.658 --> 00:04:01.205
I'm already old,

43
00:04:01.205 --> 00:04:03.974
and I drank alcohol and smoked a lot all my life.

44
00:04:08.746 --> 00:04:11.348
- Please help yourselves.
- Thank you.

45
00:04:12.349 --> 00:04:14.251
Honey, drink this.

46
00:04:15.319 --> 00:04:17.020
Aren't you cold?

47
00:04:17.020 --> 00:04:18.689
Cold in these clothes and this weather?

48
00:04:18.689 --> 00:04:21.525
Catching a cold would be a tragedy!

49
00:04:21.525 --> 00:04:22.960
I'll go get a blanket.

50
00:04:22.960 --> 00:04:24.992
Leave this on.

51
00:04:24.992 --> 00:04:26.696
I'm roasting.

52
00:04:28.732 --> 00:04:30.967
I'll be back in a moment.

53
00:04:36.430 --> 00:04:38.609
Even the youngest got a job,

54
00:04:38.609 --> 00:04:42.005
all my children
They send us more than enough money.

55
00:04:42.005 --> 00:04:45.072
I was going to travel the world with my wife,

56
00:04:45.072 --> 00:04:47.717
but I ended up with this crappy disease.

57
00:04:49.359 --> 00:04:51.822
Last year, when we took that trip,

58
00:04:51.822 --> 00:04:55.559
my wife wanted to use her miles
to go in business class.

59
00:04:55.559 --> 00:04:58.442
I told him no, that it seemed like a waste,
but now I regret it.

60
00:04:58.442 --> 00:05:01.197
Get well quickly and travel.

61
00:05:02.633 --> 00:05:04.629
Do you think I'll ever be able to use those miles?

62
00:05:04.629 --> 00:05:06.270
Of course.

63
00:05:06.270 --> 00:05:08.906
- You have to use them.
- Why do you say that?

64
00:05:08.906 --> 00:05:10.641
You're right.

65
00:05:10.641 --> 00:05:13.730
I have to heal and travel like crazy.

66
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.245
No regrets.

67
00:05:24.560 --> 00:05:27.334
I know I shouldn't say this,

68
00:05:27.334 --> 00:05:29.380
but I'm more concerned about who takes care of him

69
00:05:29.380 --> 00:05:33.596
than the patient.

70
00:05:36.033 --> 00:05:38.568
They are very happy people,

71
00:05:38.568 --> 00:05:40.804
They will get through this without problems.

72
00:05:44.841 --> 00:05:47.500
It stuck with me

73
00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:49.446
something I saw written on a tombstone.

74
00:05:51.014 --> 00:05:53.133
"I knew this would happen

75
00:05:53.133 --> 00:05:55.185
while I doubted."

76
00:05:57.203 --> 00:06:00.290
I swore I wouldn't live like this,

77
00:06:00.290 --> 00:06:02.534
but I fell into indecision again

78
00:06:02.534 --> 00:06:04.627
and I didn't move forward.

79
00:06:07.364 --> 00:06:09.733
I will live my way

80
00:06:10.434 --> 00:06:13.157
and my children will discover theirs.

81
00:06:13.157 --> 00:06:15.233
I will do everything possible

82
00:06:15.233 --> 00:06:17.173
for leading a happy life, no matter what.

83
00:06:28.452 --> 00:06:30.587
Father, what are you looking for?

84
00:06:30.587 --> 00:06:33.426
Do you know where the tent is?

85
00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:34.707
The tent?

86
00:06:34.707 --> 00:06:35.992
Yes.

87
00:06:36.994 --> 00:06:39.362
The one we use for withdrawals.

88
00:06:43.734 --> 00:06:46.797
If everything had gone well with Jun Kyung,

89
00:06:46.797 --> 00:06:49.667
I wouldn't have stayed idly
as brother-in-law

90
00:06:49.667 --> 00:06:50.853
Clear.

91
00:06:50.853 --> 00:06:52.949
You are lucky,
I chose the priesthood and not love.

92
00:06:52.949 --> 00:06:55.546
It's the only reason you're still alive.

93
00:06:55.546 --> 00:06:57.347
Sure, thanks.

94
00:06:58.065 --> 00:07:00.525
Return it before the summer retreat.

95
00:07:00.525 --> 00:07:02.466
I don't think you'll last that long.

96
00:07:02.466 --> 00:07:04.621
I'll give it back to you by then.

97
00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:07.490
Seriously, I will! OK?

98
00:07:08.558 --> 00:07:11.061
I promise, I'll return it.

99
00:07:11.061 --> 00:07:13.697
Your father has many worries,

100
00:07:13.697 --> 00:07:16.105
I don't know if I'm doing the right thing.

101
00:07:16.105 --> 00:07:17.563
Come on.

102
00:07:18.934 --> 00:07:21.705
Seriously, don't tell dad.

103
00:07:21.705 --> 00:07:24.040
Consider it a confessional secret.

104
00:07:25.685 --> 00:07:28.411
Promise it to whoever could have been your brother-in-law.

105
00:07:29.613 --> 00:07:30.916
Do it.

106
00:07:33.183 --> 00:07:34.684
Alright.

107
00:07:38.321 --> 00:07:40.590
Seriously, you can't say a word.

108
00:07:41.684 --> 00:07:43.460
Swear to God.

109
00:07:49.633 --> 00:07:51.901
<i>I came back for you.</i>

110
00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:54.971
<i>I want to try again.</i>

111
00:08:42.420 --> 00:08:44.554
Won't it be too much for her?

112
00:08:45.880 --> 00:08:49.259
I have never seen a woman
feel overwhelmed by a diamond.

113
00:08:49.259 --> 00:08:52.529
Generally,
Men are the ones who feel the burden.

114
00:08:52.529 --> 00:08:56.333
The woman who receives it will be happy.

115
00:08:56.333 --> 00:08:59.620
Sincerity is what matters most.

116
00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:02.506
And if the man knows how to live up to it,

117
00:09:02.506 --> 00:09:05.642
That will make her even happier.

118
00:09:11.462 --> 00:09:13.816
<i>What did I do so wrong?</i>

119
00:09:15.852 --> 00:09:18.847
<i>I worked until I was tired
to earn the money.</i>

120
00:09:18.847 --> 00:09:21.891
<i>I will sell the house that I bought with so much effort.</i>

121
00:09:23.527 --> 00:09:26.233
<i>It's time to look for my happiness.</i>

122
00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:28.598
<i>Do I deserve to be hated so much for that?</i>

123
00:09:34.671 --> 00:09:37.106
What's up?

124
00:09:38.508 --> 00:09:41.110
When you're worried, you go for a walk.

125
00:09:41.735 --> 00:09:44.814
But your house is quite far away,
Isn't that a lot?

126
00:09:46.416 --> 00:09:48.816
Jun Kyung, come up, hurry up.

127
00:09:48.816 --> 00:09:50.587
I'm sorry.

128
00:09:53.715 --> 00:09:55.320
Even if it is your house,

129
00:09:55.320 --> 00:09:57.961
I don't understand why you want to sell it out of nowhere.

130
00:09:57.961 --> 00:09:59.091
And I don't understand Jun Seo,

131
00:09:59.091 --> 00:10:02.098
He lost his temper and it's not even his house.

132
00:10:02.832 --> 00:10:06.069
They are adults, what's wrong with them?

133
00:10:08.305 --> 00:10:10.974
I think I understand it.

134
00:10:12.876 --> 00:10:15.044
Since when are you so understanding?

135
00:10:16.980 --> 00:10:20.150
Not only do I understand it, the truth is, I admire it.

136
00:10:20.150 --> 00:10:21.138
Because?

137
00:10:21.138 --> 00:10:22.686
your father

138
00:10:22.686 --> 00:10:25.668
made a very brave decision

139
00:10:25.668 --> 00:10:28.758
to be with the person you love.

140
00:10:29.834 --> 00:10:31.728
It's admirable.

141
00:10:31.728 --> 00:10:33.658
Where do you find a man like that?

142
00:10:33.658 --> 00:10:36.598
He is not just a man, he is also a father.

143
00:10:36.598 --> 00:10:38.935
You moved,

144
00:10:38.935 --> 00:10:42.995
and Jun Seo is barely home
between school and appointments.

145
00:10:43.751 --> 00:10:45.508
Your father is alone there,

146
00:10:45.508 --> 00:10:47.344
It is logical what you feel.

147
00:10:47.344 --> 00:10:49.292
She could move in and live with him.

148
00:10:49.292 --> 00:10:50.852
Do you think she would feel comfortable?

149
00:10:50.852 --> 00:10:53.149
Jun Seo wouldn't be either.

150
00:10:59.390 --> 00:11:01.392
That?

151
00:11:01.392 --> 00:11:04.961
That's why I like you.

152
00:11:13.164 --> 00:11:15.772
Being a father, being a man...

153
00:11:18.400 --> 00:11:20.877
I'm not good at that either, it's difficult.

154
00:11:23.146 --> 00:11:24.981
It's difficult.

155
00:11:26.116 --> 00:11:29.025
I moved a while ago,

156
00:11:29.025 --> 00:11:32.355
I thought that house didn't mean much to me.

157
00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:36.693
Now that I think it will disappear,

158
00:11:36.693 --> 00:11:38.828
I feel strange.

159
00:11:47.637 --> 00:11:50.140
It is very well preserved.

160
00:11:50.140 --> 00:11:51.162
He has his years,

161
00:11:51.162 --> 00:11:54.778
but the floors and trim are immaculate.

162
00:11:54.778 --> 00:11:57.397
It is ready to move in and live in.

163
00:11:57.397 --> 00:11:58.655
Oh really?

164
00:11:58.655 --> 00:12:00.984
It's the first time I've sold a house.

165
00:12:00.984 --> 00:12:02.870
I envy you.

166
00:12:02.870 --> 00:12:04.977
Even if it's your first time, you'll sell it.

167
00:12:04.977 --> 00:12:07.924
I don't have my own house to sell.

168
00:12:12.463 --> 00:12:13.968
No.

169
00:12:13.968 --> 00:12:17.400
You have to pan with the phone
from here

170
00:12:17.400 --> 00:12:20.143
to make it appear wider.

171
00:12:20.143 --> 00:12:21.538
I've told you a million times.

172
00:12:21.538 --> 00:12:22.834
Excuse me,

173
00:12:22.834 --> 00:12:24.843
How long do you think it will take to sell the house?

174
00:12:24.843 --> 00:12:26.583
The truth,

175
00:12:26.583 --> 00:12:28.266
you would be surprised by the number of people

176
00:12:28.266 --> 00:12:30.714
who are looking for a house with a patio like this.

177
00:12:30.714 --> 00:12:33.550
It is ideal for raising children and having dogs.

178
00:12:33.550 --> 00:12:36.263
A property like this
It could be sold tomorrow.

179
00:12:36.263 --> 00:12:37.554
I see.

180
00:12:37.554 --> 00:12:39.291
We will upload the photos and videos

181
00:12:39.291 --> 00:12:41.525
to our blog immediately.

182
00:12:41.525 --> 00:12:42.874
So fast?

183
00:12:42.874 --> 00:12:43.715
Sure,

184
00:12:43.715 --> 00:12:47.196
You have to be fast to survive today.

185
00:12:49.901 --> 00:12:51.233
Over there.

186
00:12:51.233 --> 00:12:53.102
Yes, like that.

187
00:12:54.671 --> 00:12:56.407
Did he guarantee it to you?

188
00:12:56.407 --> 00:12:58.214
Will he assign you the position of professor?

189
00:12:58.214 --> 00:13:01.511
It's not an official decision yet.

190
00:13:03.013 --> 00:13:05.534
but he said he would recommend me.

191
00:13:05.534 --> 00:13:07.171
Trust me.

192
00:13:07.171 --> 00:13:10.087
Why would I trust anyone?
who is still in college

193
00:13:10.087 --> 00:13:12.321
Why didn't he get enough credits?

194
00:13:14.058 --> 00:13:15.992
For your patience and persistence?

195
00:13:18.528 --> 00:13:20.097
It may be,

196
00:13:20.097 --> 00:13:22.265
They are also great virtues.

197
00:13:24.267 --> 00:13:26.133
By the way,

198
00:13:26.133 --> 00:13:29.772
you criticized your dad
for selling the house without consulting you,

199
00:13:30.240 --> 00:13:33.265
and now you settle here without asking me?

200
00:13:33.265 --> 00:13:36.980
We should share the land,

201
00:13:36.980 --> 00:13:40.250
and also a little of your food.

202
00:13:40.250 --> 00:13:42.853
As for the bathroom...

203
00:13:42.853 --> 00:13:44.408
How about I use it when you're away?

204
00:13:44.408 --> 00:13:46.256
When I am a teacher,

205
00:13:46.256 --> 00:13:48.353
I will leave immediately, even if you cry

206
00:13:48.353 --> 00:13:49.993
and beg me not to do it.

207
00:13:49.993 --> 00:13:52.148
Don't worry.

208
00:13:52.148 --> 00:13:53.563
Heavens.

209
00:13:58.902 --> 00:14:00.636
But tell me,

210
00:14:01.133 --> 00:14:03.836
do you really want to be a teacher?

211
00:14:03.836 --> 00:14:05.308
Starting today,

212
00:14:05.308 --> 00:14:08.267
I start again

213
00:14:08.267 --> 00:14:10.247
like a man born to be a teacher.

214
00:14:10.247 --> 00:14:11.629
Because?

215
00:14:11.629 --> 00:14:13.189
Because I need revenge

216
00:14:13.189 --> 00:14:15.574
from the humiliation and insults of my family.

217
00:14:18.505 --> 00:14:20.758
You must not tell anyone that I am here.

218
00:14:20.758 --> 00:14:22.091
Understood?

219
00:14:24.061 --> 00:14:25.528
Understood?

220
00:14:27.328 --> 00:14:30.400
<i>Jun Seo is at my house.</i>

221
00:14:30.400 --> 00:14:33.536
<i>I thought you and Jin Ho would be worried.</i>

222
00:14:37.774 --> 00:14:38.909
I already know.

223
00:14:38.909 --> 00:14:41.245
<i>How did you know?</i>

224
00:14:41.245 --> 00:14:43.213
The priest told me.

225
00:14:43.213 --> 00:14:44.935
Chang Sik?

226
00:14:44.935 --> 00:14:46.883
How did you know?

227
00:14:46.883 --> 00:14:48.184
I won't worry anymore.

228
00:14:48.184 --> 00:14:49.636
Jun Seo will figure it out.

229
00:14:49.636 --> 00:14:52.456
Like you said, he's not a boy.

230
00:14:52.456 --> 00:14:54.367
Something else,

231
00:14:54.367 --> 00:14:56.425
I put the house up for sale

232
00:14:57.928 --> 00:14:59.395
<i>so that you know.</i>

233
00:15:01.888 --> 00:15:03.199
Okay.

234
00:15:13.343 --> 00:15:14.721
- Hello.
- Hello.

235
00:15:14.721 --> 00:15:16.646
Yes, please come in.

236
00:15:16.646 --> 00:15:18.200
- Come in, please.
- Permission.

237
00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:19.516
- Hello.
- Hello.

238
00:15:19.516 --> 00:15:21.201
Let's start the tour inside.

239
00:15:21.201 --> 00:15:23.988
- Yes, go ahead, take your time.
- Thank you.

240
00:15:23.988 --> 00:15:25.621
Let's go this way.

241
00:15:34.667 --> 00:15:35.632
Help yourselves,

242
00:15:35.632 --> 00:15:37.600
drink while you watch calmly.

243
00:15:37.600 --> 00:15:39.035
Thank you.

244
00:15:39.035 --> 00:15:40.836
Thank you.

245
00:15:42.005 --> 00:15:44.367
It is very deteriorated.

246
00:15:44.367 --> 00:15:46.353
It didn't look like that in the video.

247
00:15:46.353 --> 00:15:48.678
It's very old-fashioned, isn't it?

248
00:15:49.573 --> 00:15:51.734
When we redo the wallpaper and floors,

249
00:15:51.734 --> 00:15:54.218
We should change all the doors.

250
00:15:54.218 --> 00:15:56.185
Of course, they should change them.

251
00:15:59.752 --> 00:16:02.559
Judging by their style, they have very good taste,

252
00:16:02.559 --> 00:16:04.928
so i bet
because they will decorate the house very well.

253
00:17:44.727 --> 00:17:47.846
The room is a little small
for the size of the house.

254
00:17:47.846 --> 00:17:51.133
You said that one room for the baby is enough
and another one,

255
00:17:51.606 --> 00:17:54.672
so could you tear down this wall
and unify the rooms.

256
00:17:54.672 --> 00:17:55.971
Is it safe...

257
00:17:58.374 --> 00:17:59.757
tear down the wall?

258
00:17:59.757 --> 00:18:01.720
Old houses are more resistant.

259
00:18:01.720 --> 00:18:03.146
The construction is like a fort.

260
00:18:03.146 --> 00:18:04.914
Throw it down and you're done.

261
00:18:09.034 --> 00:18:11.658
Will there be many insects in summer?

262
00:18:11.658 --> 00:18:13.601
Anyway, we don't need a garden.

263
00:18:13.601 --> 00:18:15.358
What if we built a terrace here?

264
00:18:15.358 --> 00:18:17.668
Yes, if you put a terrace

265
00:18:17.668 --> 00:18:19.763
with an umbrella,

266
00:18:19.763 --> 00:18:21.765
You won't have to go to a cafe.

267
00:18:24.333 --> 00:18:25.902
That's enough.

268
00:18:25.902 --> 00:18:27.567
If you don't like the house, don't buy it.

269
00:18:27.567 --> 00:18:29.454
Why do they talk nonsense about demolishing

270
00:18:29.454 --> 00:18:30.506
and renovate someone else's house?

271
00:18:30.506 --> 00:18:32.167
Mr. Seo,

272
00:18:32.167 --> 00:18:35.490
They want to improve it because they like it.

273
00:18:35.490 --> 00:18:38.082
This guy is ridiculous.

274
00:18:38.082 --> 00:18:39.350
Am I ridiculous?

275
00:18:39.350 --> 00:18:40.850
What's so ridiculous about me?

276
00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:42.953
You two are the ridiculous ones.

277
00:18:42.953 --> 00:18:44.721
They have no idea what kind of house this is.

278
00:18:44.721 --> 00:18:46.355
I won't sell it, so leave.

279
00:18:46.355 --> 00:18:47.891
I think there is a misunderstanding.

280
00:18:47.891 --> 00:18:50.693
And you are the worst! Oh really!

281
00:18:50.693 --> 00:18:52.211
You said it didn't need fixing.

282
00:18:52.211 --> 00:18:53.011
Get out of here.

283
00:18:53.011 --> 00:18:53.871
I won't sell it to you.

284
00:18:53.871 --> 00:18:55.235
Get out of here.

285
00:18:55.235 --> 00:18:56.332
- Out.
- Mr. Seo.

286
00:18:56.332 --> 00:18:57.667
Get out of here!

287
00:18:57.667 --> 00:18:58.356
Mr. Seo?

288
00:18:58.356 --> 00:19:00.104
Yes.

289
00:19:00.104 --> 00:19:01.575
I think it turned out well.

290
00:19:01.575 --> 00:19:03.335
I'll be in touch.

291
00:19:03.335 --> 00:19:04.895
OK.

292
00:19:04.895 --> 00:19:05.756
Yes that's fine.

293
00:19:05.756 --> 00:19:07.015
Come on.

294
00:19:07.015 --> 00:19:08.777
Thanks for showing us the house.

295
00:19:19.122 --> 00:19:20.789
My mom...

296
00:19:21.624 --> 00:19:25.728
did he act badly with you that day?

297
00:19:26.336 --> 00:19:27.796
No.

298
00:19:29.366 --> 00:19:31.734
I think so.

299
00:19:33.788 --> 00:19:35.771
But please

300
00:19:36.634 --> 00:19:39.275
don't hate her.

301
00:19:40.344 --> 00:19:42.378
I don't hate her.

302
00:19:45.214 --> 00:19:47.216
Since I won't live here anymore,

303
00:19:47.216 --> 00:19:48.684
you can be calmer.

304
00:19:48.684 --> 00:19:50.916
You can sleep at my dad's house.

305
00:19:50.916 --> 00:19:53.355
You talk like you're never going to see me again.

306
00:19:54.425 --> 00:19:56.425
Why not?

307
00:19:57.318 --> 00:19:59.195
If you and my dad

308
00:19:59.834 --> 00:20:01.734
they separate,

309
00:20:01.734 --> 00:20:04.101
will you stop seeing me?

310
00:20:04.101 --> 00:20:05.401
That?

311
00:20:06.233 --> 00:20:07.570
Well,

312
00:20:08.237 --> 00:20:10.400
You never know with people.

313
00:20:10.400 --> 00:20:11.674
I say,

314
00:20:11.674 --> 00:20:14.410
It's not that I want them to stop going out.

315
00:20:15.011 --> 00:20:16.679
My dad...

316
00:20:19.534 --> 00:20:21.784
He is a very good guy.

317
00:20:23.764 --> 00:20:26.656
Your Korean has improved a lot!

318
00:20:26.656 --> 00:20:29.358
You can now say what you want.

319
00:20:48.511 --> 00:20:50.372
Did you also bring the fish?

320
00:20:50.372 --> 00:20:52.082
Well...

321
00:20:52.082 --> 00:20:53.315
yes.

322
00:20:53.883 --> 00:20:55.686
Because? Do you hate it?

323
00:20:55.686 --> 00:20:56.823
No.

324
00:20:56.823 --> 00:20:58.220
Let's go in.

325
00:21:08.966 --> 00:21:10.363
Leave.

326
00:21:10.363 --> 00:21:11.302
Good luck unpacking.

327
00:21:11.302 --> 00:21:12.403
That?

328
00:21:12.403 --> 00:21:14.737
Will Daniel and I carry all this alone?

329
00:21:15.906 --> 00:21:18.042
It's not that much.

330
00:21:18.042 --> 00:21:20.109
You don't have to record today, right?

331
00:21:21.177 --> 00:21:24.697
You are not prohibited from being here,
so stay for dinner.

332
00:21:24.697 --> 00:21:26.237
You like curry.

333
00:21:26.237 --> 00:21:27.997
For the first time, I cooked with enthusiasm.

334
00:21:27.997 --> 00:21:29.785
I agreed to see Jun Kyung.

335
00:21:35.859 --> 00:21:37.817
Okay,

336
00:21:37.817 --> 00:21:40.437
I won't rush you.

337
00:21:40.437 --> 00:21:43.767
We'll still have to see each other for Daniel.

338
00:21:43.767 --> 00:21:45.534
I have a lot of time.

339
00:21:46.236 --> 00:21:47.636
Leave.

340
00:22:54.318 --> 00:22:56.038
Hello, Jun Seo.

341
00:22:57.141 --> 00:22:58.741
Will you be late again?

342
00:22:59.321 --> 00:23:01.744
You are working a lot.

343
00:23:01.744 --> 00:23:03.879
Eat something.

344
00:23:04.403 --> 00:23:05.897
OK.

345
00:24:19.100 --> 00:24:21.400
<i>When I was little,</i>

346
00:24:21.400 --> 00:24:23.993
<i>Mom always brought freshly washed clothes</i>

347
00:24:23.993 --> 00:24:26.462
<i>and he folded it on the living room floor</i>

348
00:24:27.233 --> 00:24:29.765
more or less at this time.

349
00:24:30.534 --> 00:24:34.570
I always sat next to her and helped her.

350
00:24:35.324 --> 00:24:38.440
Although it made a mess and was folded badly,

351
00:24:38.962 --> 00:24:41.812
mom said he was a good boy

352
00:24:41.812 --> 00:24:44.112
and that he did it very well.

353
00:24:45.062 --> 00:24:46.815
Then

354
00:24:47.367 --> 00:24:49.251
Jun Kyung was coming home from school.

355
00:24:50.082 --> 00:24:52.154
A little later,

356
00:24:53.534 --> 00:24:56.391
dad came back from work,

357
00:24:57.293 --> 00:25:00.996
we all had dinner together

358
00:25:01.743 --> 00:25:05.734
and we ate ice cream because mom loved it.

359
00:25:06.901 --> 00:25:09.071
It's a nice memory.

360
00:25:10.739 --> 00:25:13.175
Our family was very happy then.

361
00:25:28.034 --> 00:25:29.233
Hello?

362
00:25:29.233 --> 00:25:31.001
It's me.

363
00:25:31.001 --> 00:25:32.861
Are you done yet?

364
00:25:34.167 --> 00:25:37.333
It must have made you sad to see Daniel go.

365
00:25:37.333 --> 00:25:38.934
<i>Yes.</i>

366
00:25:38.934 --> 00:25:41.703
When I return home, Daniel will not be there,

367
00:25:42.233 --> 00:25:43.874
Oscar won't be...

368
00:25:43.874 --> 00:25:46.157
The only thing that will move in that house

369
00:25:46.157 --> 00:25:48.677
It will be the robot vacuum cleaner.

370
00:25:53.282 --> 00:25:55.711
Maybe I should get out of there.

371
00:25:55.711 --> 00:25:57.734
<i>The lease ends anyway.</i>

372
00:25:57.734 --> 00:25:59.456
<i>I need a place that suits me better,</i>

373
00:25:59.456 --> 00:26:02.524
something where I can live alone.

374
00:26:07.801 --> 00:26:09.731
<i>Where are you now?</i>

375
00:26:12.197 --> 00:26:15.706
I'm in my father's house,
but there is no one.

376
00:26:15.706 --> 00:26:18.257
<i>What are you doing there alone?</i>

377
00:26:18.257 --> 00:26:19.808
I'm...

378
00:26:20.734 --> 00:26:22.477
sitting.

379
00:26:28.026 --> 00:26:30.385
Here alone...

380
00:26:31.445 --> 00:26:34.556
I understand what my father feels,
just like you said.

381
00:26:35.437 --> 00:26:39.061
I don't think I can object
to sell the house now.

382
00:26:43.095 --> 00:26:44.600
Jun Kyung.

383
00:26:45.336 --> 00:26:46.602
<i>What?</i>

384
00:26:48.706 --> 00:26:50.606
What if we move in together?

385
00:26:54.599 --> 00:26:56.946
But how inopportune!

386
00:26:56.946 --> 00:27:00.115
How are they going to denigrate the house in front of the owner?

387
00:27:00.115 --> 00:27:02.217
I feel offended just hearing it.

388
00:27:04.678 --> 00:27:08.891
How can they not do it?
If the owner puts the house up for sale

389
00:27:08.891 --> 00:27:11.059
Like it doesn't mean anything to him?

390
00:27:11.732 --> 00:27:14.164
Taking Bom's things away was horrible,

391
00:27:14.164 --> 00:27:18.133
It was like I fell apart
of every shared moment.

392
00:27:22.338 --> 00:27:25.007
It's not a lack of affection

393
00:27:25.007 --> 00:27:28.577
which leads us to do it.

394
00:27:34.183 --> 00:27:35.984
Wait.

395
00:27:40.824 --> 00:27:42.391
Hello?

396
00:27:46.306 --> 00:27:47.692
[Seo Jun Kyung]

397
00:27:47.692 --> 00:27:48.997
What?

398
00:27:55.439 --> 00:27:56.974
You scared me!

399
00:27:56.974 --> 00:27:58.832
Why don't you answer my calls?

400
00:27:58.832 --> 00:28:00.544
How did you know I was here?

401
00:28:00.544 --> 00:28:02.544
Is your location top secret information?

402
00:28:04.747 --> 00:28:05.712
That?

403
00:28:05.712 --> 00:28:09.092
I can't trust anyone anymore.

404
00:28:09.092 --> 00:28:10.454
Don't tell dad, it's a secret.

405
00:28:10.454 --> 00:28:13.017
Dad already knows.

406
00:28:14.605 --> 00:28:16.324
Did you tell him?

407
00:28:17.409 --> 00:28:20.049
Didn't you hear me?

408
00:28:20.049 --> 00:28:22.849
It must have been Chang Sik!

409
00:28:22.849 --> 00:28:26.003
How can a priest be so gossipy?

410
00:28:26.003 --> 00:28:28.370
Get out of there.

411
00:28:29.873 --> 00:28:31.540
Where are we going?

412
00:28:33.410 --> 00:28:35.377
Tell me first.

413
00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:38.280
Isn't Do Hyun's idea great?

414
00:28:38.280 --> 00:28:41.917
If we leave where we live
and we rent this house,

415
00:28:41.917 --> 00:28:43.834
We won't have to sell it.

416
00:28:43.834 --> 00:28:46.555
Dad, you can run the camp
with Ja Yeong,

417
00:28:46.555 --> 00:28:48.993
and Jun Seo can stay in his room.

418
00:28:48.993 --> 00:28:50.327
By no means.

419
00:28:50.327 --> 00:28:52.238
I'm not going to benefit from you.

420
00:28:52.238 --> 00:28:54.196
Shut up, you stubborn brat.

421
00:28:54.196 --> 00:28:56.219
This time I'm going to get ahead alone.

422
00:28:56.219 --> 00:28:59.968
Enough, you're a burden on Hye On.

423
00:28:59.968 --> 00:29:01.319
It is not a burden.

424
00:29:01.319 --> 00:29:04.940
It's a relief to have Jun Seo around...

425
00:29:06.110 --> 00:29:08.344
Well, maybe not so much.

426
00:29:08.344 --> 00:29:11.649
But he works as a bodyguard for free,

427
00:29:11.649 --> 00:29:13.215
so I like it.

428
00:29:17.720 --> 00:29:19.960
What do you think?

429
00:29:19.960 --> 00:29:23.240
Can I comment?

430
00:29:23.240 --> 00:29:24.620
Of course.

431
00:29:24.620 --> 00:29:27.381
It would not be necessary to sell the house,

432
00:29:27.381 --> 00:29:29.640
so I totally agree.

433
00:29:29.640 --> 00:29:30.932
Good idea, right?

434
00:29:31.535 --> 00:29:34.580
Do you really agree?

435
00:29:34.580 --> 00:29:36.940
Now you're in love,

436
00:29:36.940 --> 00:29:39.294
but that won't be forever.

437
00:29:39.294 --> 00:29:41.845
What will happen to the house
When does money get involved?

438
00:29:41.845 --> 00:29:43.080
It seems perfect to me.

439
00:29:43.080 --> 00:29:45.247
If the house prevents us from separating, even better.

440
00:29:54.558 --> 00:29:56.291
What do you think, dad?

441
00:30:08.971 --> 00:30:10.539
Dad?

442
00:30:11.834 --> 00:30:13.375
I think...

443
00:30:20.167 --> 00:30:22.350
If that's okay with you...

444
00:30:31.693 --> 00:30:34.365
Is this another dad tantrum?

445
00:30:34.365 --> 00:30:37.365
Is it a baby or what?

446
00:30:37.365 --> 00:30:40.302
One more word, and I'll sew your mouth shut.

447
00:30:47.434 --> 00:30:49.277
What's happening?

448
00:31:03.258 --> 00:31:04.993
this house

449
00:31:05.701 --> 00:31:08.363
It's not just part of my past.

450
00:31:09.734 --> 00:31:12.267
Also save your story,

451
00:31:12.267 --> 00:31:14.769
Jun Seo's

452
00:31:15.300 --> 00:31:18.840
and Mi Ran's, belongs to all of us.

453
00:31:20.709 --> 00:31:23.378
I have been selfish and weak.

454
00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:27.482
I can't even look at their faces.

455
00:31:36.927 --> 00:31:38.894
No.

456
00:31:40.567 --> 00:31:42.697
The day we moved,

457
00:31:43.739 --> 00:31:46.316
I asked myself if we deserved a house like that.

458
00:31:46.316 --> 00:31:48.015
I didn't sleep a wink,

459
00:31:48.015 --> 00:31:49.804
The rent always left us on the edge.

460
00:31:50.941 --> 00:31:53.675
Mom loved living here.

461
00:31:55.102 --> 00:31:59.047
Your mom and I loved this house.

462
00:31:59.047 --> 00:32:01.934
We went from a monthly rental
to a large deposit,

463
00:32:01.934 --> 00:32:04.252
and in the end it ended up being ours.

464
00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:08.423
The night we made it
we started crying.

465
00:32:13.629 --> 00:32:17.265
Your mom was very careful with money
at that time,

466
00:32:18.235 --> 00:32:20.402
he made a great effort.

467
00:32:21.069 --> 00:32:23.567
Here he had Jun Seo,

468
00:32:23.567 --> 00:32:25.507
I raised you

469
00:32:27.233 --> 00:32:29.577
and he also supported me.

470
00:32:35.719 --> 00:32:37.203
Look,

471
00:32:38.186 --> 00:32:40.422
I'm sure your mom told me everything

472
00:32:41.834 --> 00:32:43.970
from up there.

473
00:32:43.970 --> 00:32:46.561
Knowing mom's temperament,
do you think not?

474
00:32:54.406 --> 00:32:58.309
Your mom and me
We had you when we were 20 years old.

475
00:32:58.309 --> 00:33:00.342
We didn't know what to do,

476
00:33:01.436 --> 00:33:03.878
We were kids raising a baby.

477
00:33:08.470 --> 00:33:11.420
<i>It seems like we raised you, but...</i>

478
00:33:11.420 --> 00:33:13.121
- Hey.
- That?

479
00:33:13.121 --> 00:33:15.867
<i>...you made us parents...</i>

480
00:33:15.867 --> 00:33:16.735
What time is it?

481
00:33:16.735 --> 00:33:18.860
<i>-...and in adults.</i>
- It's six.

482
00:33:20.901 --> 00:33:22.498
<i>Here, in this place...</i>

483
00:33:22.498 --> 00:33:23.932
Wait.

484
00:33:23.932 --> 00:33:25.800
<i>...you and me</i>

485
00:33:26.867 --> 00:33:28.937
<i>we grew up together.</i>

486
00:33:32.867 --> 00:33:34.367
Hey.

487
00:33:34.367 --> 00:33:36.146
Do you remember that moment?

488
00:33:36.146 --> 00:33:37.314
Which?

489
00:33:37.314 --> 00:33:41.282
When you looked at the sky with me here.

490
00:33:47.923 --> 00:33:50.995
Dad, where are we going?

491
00:33:50.995 --> 00:33:52.718
Did you wake up?

492
00:33:52.718 --> 00:33:55.397
It's Lunar New Year,
We should go to grandma's house.

493
00:34:00.569 --> 00:34:02.304
- Dad.
- That?

494
00:34:02.304 --> 00:34:04.773
Why does the sky look like this?

495
00:34:07.278 --> 00:34:10.012
It's called dawn.

496
00:34:10.012 --> 00:34:11.290
Sunrise?

497
00:34:11.290 --> 00:34:12.391
Yeah.

498
00:34:12.391 --> 00:34:15.491
It must be the first time you see it.

499
00:34:15.491 --> 00:34:17.154
Isn't it beautiful?

500
00:34:17.154 --> 00:34:19.154
It's lovely.

501
00:34:19.857 --> 00:34:20.951
Dad.

502
00:34:20.951 --> 00:34:21.750
Yeah?

503
00:34:21.750 --> 00:34:25.560
Thank you for showing me the sunrise.

504
00:34:26.897 --> 00:34:28.371
Yeah,

505
00:34:28.371 --> 00:34:30.098
Of course.

506
00:34:31.368 --> 00:34:32.531
Dear!

507
00:34:32.531 --> 00:34:34.131
We'll be late!

508
00:34:34.131 --> 00:34:35.873
Yes, I'm coming.

509
00:34:35.873 --> 00:34:36.768
Let's go.

510
00:34:36.768 --> 00:34:38.606
Did you wake up?

511
00:34:48.252 --> 00:34:50.585
That is very heavy.

512
00:34:54.100 --> 00:34:55.390
- That's yours, right?
- That?

513
00:34:55.390 --> 00:34:56.791
- The backpack?
- Yes, the backpack.

514
00:34:57.995 --> 00:34:59.068
- Yes Yeong.
- Yeah?

515
00:34:59.068 --> 00:35:01.463
Grab the box above.

516
00:35:12.689 --> 00:35:14.317
- Happens.
- Yes, thanks.

517
00:35:14.317 --> 00:35:16.311
It shows that it weighs.

518
00:35:22.380 --> 00:35:23.437
Jun Kyung.

519
00:35:23.437 --> 00:35:24.586
Yeah.

520
00:35:28.258 --> 00:35:31.695
I left your mom's bed untouched, like you said.

521
00:35:31.695 --> 00:35:32.794
OK.

522
00:35:32.794 --> 00:35:34.390
We will use my room,

523
00:35:34.390 --> 00:35:37.599
and we will leave the main one and Jun Seo's.

524
00:35:56.983 --> 00:35:58.887
Well,

525
00:35:58.887 --> 00:36:00.567
let's keep in touch,

526
00:36:00.567 --> 00:36:02.457
let's see each other often

527
00:36:02.457 --> 00:36:04.634
and, finally,

528
00:36:04.634 --> 00:36:06.328
Let's all take good care of ourselves.

529
00:36:06.328 --> 00:36:07.529
- You too.
- You too.

530
00:36:07.529 --> 00:36:08.697
Come to the camp.

531
00:36:08.697 --> 00:36:11.035
- Sure, we'll go.
- We will pass often.

532
00:36:11.035 --> 00:36:12.436
- We're leaving.
- OK.

533
00:36:12.436 --> 00:36:14.669
- Drive carefully.
- Leave.

534
00:36:14.669 --> 00:36:15.564
Drive carefully.

535
00:36:15.564 --> 00:36:17.458
- Drive carefully, dad.
- Yes.

536
00:36:24.273 --> 00:36:24.981
We're leaving.

537
00:36:24.981 --> 00:36:26.295
How should I handle this?

538
00:36:26.295 --> 00:36:28.635
Fire them and that's it. Stop bothering Hye On.

539
00:36:28.635 --> 00:36:30.215
Treat it well.

540
00:36:30.215 --> 00:36:32.520
- See you later.
- We're leaving.

541
00:36:38.260 --> 00:36:40.328
I told you I would take care of the luggage.

542
00:36:40.898 --> 00:36:43.198
What the hell are you bringing here?

543
00:36:45.534 --> 00:36:47.001
What is this?

544
00:36:53.010 --> 00:36:54.776
Thank you.

545
00:36:57.601 --> 00:36:59.106
Wait...

546
00:37:09.701 --> 00:37:11.626
One moment,

547
00:37:11.626 --> 00:37:13.795
This chair isn't bad at all, right?

548
00:37:27.348 --> 00:37:28.712
Ja Yeong.

549
00:37:28.712 --> 00:37:29.813
That?

550
00:37:29.813 --> 00:37:31.379
Come here, quickly.

551
00:37:31.379 --> 00:37:33.014
- What's happening?
- Come on, hurry up!

552
00:37:33.014 --> 00:37:34.518
- What's happening?
- Hurry up!

553
00:37:34.518 --> 00:37:36.089
- It's huge.
- That?

554
00:37:36.089 --> 00:37:37.919
Look there.

555
00:37:43.034 --> 00:37:45.388
Where is the semicircle?

556
00:37:45.388 --> 00:37:48.708
You said that the Corona Borealis has that shape.

557
00:37:48.708 --> 00:37:51.348
I forgot to tell you

558
00:37:51.348 --> 00:37:53.801
that only good-hearted people can see it.

559
00:37:56.738 --> 00:37:58.134
Finally we finish.

560
00:37:58.134 --> 00:38:00.975
What a relief.

561
00:38:06.514 --> 00:38:08.116
What a difficult day, right?

562
00:38:14.122 --> 00:38:16.024
here on the terrace

563
00:38:16.567 --> 00:38:19.327
of this old house...

564
00:38:21.749 --> 00:38:24.032
Don't we look like an old couple?

565
00:38:24.032 --> 00:38:25.336
An elderly couple?

566
00:38:25.336 --> 00:38:26.567
Yes.

567
00:38:27.801 --> 00:38:29.667
like those couples

568
00:38:29.667 --> 00:38:32.076
who have lived in harmony under the same roof

569
00:38:32.076 --> 00:38:33.708
for three

570
00:38:34.878 --> 00:38:36.444
or four decades

571
00:38:37.681 --> 00:38:39.647
without major problems.

572
00:38:45.022 --> 00:38:46.801
Do you want...

573
00:38:46.801 --> 00:38:48.256
a cold beer?

574
00:38:49.226 --> 00:38:50.525
Clear!

575
00:38:52.963 --> 00:38:55.196
Fill the glass well and add ice.

576
00:38:56.731 --> 00:38:58.201
OK.

577
00:39:15.216 --> 00:39:17.085
Here's your food.

578
00:39:24.128 --> 00:39:25.660
He has a good appetite.

579
00:39:26.757 --> 00:39:29.317
Tell me when you want to visit your dad

580
00:39:29.317 --> 00:39:30.765
and I will take you.

581
00:39:32.323 --> 00:39:34.936
I think I would be out of line if I went now.

582
00:39:35.582 --> 00:39:37.522
I won't be inopportune.

583
00:39:37.522 --> 00:39:38.839
Because?

584
00:39:39.643 --> 00:39:40.914
That?

585
00:39:47.251 --> 00:39:48.475
Well...

586
00:39:49.484 --> 00:39:51.286
Dad...

587
00:39:51.286 --> 00:39:53.988
moved in with Jun Kyung.

588
00:39:54.867 --> 00:39:56.758
Didn't you know?

589
00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:03.999
Let's get our caffeine fix.

590
00:40:03.999 --> 00:40:07.071
The pantry machine is top notch.

591
00:40:07.071 --> 00:40:09.637
If the hospital coffee is so good,
why did you resign?

592
00:40:13.808 --> 00:40:15.043
By the way,

593
00:40:15.043 --> 00:40:18.013
Your family is very fashionable.

594
00:40:18.013 --> 00:40:20.181
Young people, adults, elderly...

595
00:40:20.181 --> 00:40:22.536
They all live together instead of getting married.

596
00:40:23.051 --> 00:40:24.563
How chic.

597
00:40:24.563 --> 00:40:25.920
Everyone very carefree.

598
00:40:26.462 --> 00:40:27.889
Are you criticizing me?

599
00:40:29.827 --> 00:40:33.394
Since when is being fashionable wrong?

600
00:40:35.572 --> 00:40:38.572
But be honest with me,
the rush of moving

601
00:40:38.572 --> 00:40:41.249
It had to do with the insecurity that it generated in you.

602
00:40:41.249 --> 00:40:43.117
that woman who came to stir the waters?

603
00:40:43.934 --> 00:40:44.807
Well,

604
00:40:44.807 --> 00:40:48.009
perhaps, unintentionally,
I killed two birds with one stone.

605
00:40:51.212 --> 00:40:52.213
Do you have plans for later?

606
00:40:52.213 --> 00:40:53.721
I'll go to a children's cafe with the little ones.

607
00:40:53.721 --> 00:40:55.319
Let's go together.

608
00:40:55.319 --> 00:40:56.951
Don't even dream about it.

609
00:41:01.556 --> 00:41:03.257
Hello.

610
00:41:03.761 --> 00:41:06.127
It's your lunch time, right?

611
00:41:10.868 --> 00:41:13.534
I found out that you and Do Hyun
They went to live together.

612
00:41:17.782 --> 00:41:21.242
Is it necessary to come to my workplace
to ask that?

613
00:41:24.879 --> 00:41:27.381
That doesn't interest me so much.

614
00:41:27.867 --> 00:41:31.719
Actually, I want to know if they're getting married.

615
00:41:33.791 --> 00:41:35.990
Why do you ask that?

616
00:41:38.118 --> 00:41:40.195
Someone once said

617
00:41:40.195 --> 00:41:42.901
that people go out, discuss,

618
00:41:42.901 --> 00:41:46.334
we separate, we become strangers
and then we reconnect.

619
00:41:46.334 --> 00:41:50.404
The couple is the only family that is chosen.

620
00:41:52.774 --> 00:41:54.103
Where do you want to go?

621
00:41:54.103 --> 00:41:55.735
I mean

622
00:41:55.735 --> 00:41:58.862
because it is more complicated than it seems.

623
00:41:58.862 --> 00:42:01.151
Parents or children are not chosen,
a spouse, yes.

624
00:42:01.151 --> 00:42:03.284
You can't cut ties with them.

625
00:42:04.688 --> 00:42:07.522
Do Hyun is Daniel's father.

626
00:42:07.992 --> 00:42:10.591
and I am his mother.

627
00:42:18.999 --> 00:42:21.467
I'm still not sure,

628
00:42:21.467 --> 00:42:24.906
but if we get married,
You will be the first to know.

629
00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:33.200
You know,

630
00:42:33.200 --> 00:42:35.650
every time we see each other,

631
00:42:35.650 --> 00:42:39.220
I feel like we are very similar, don't you?

632
00:42:43.491 --> 00:42:44.325
Because?

633
00:42:44.325 --> 00:42:48.002
We do not know how to express or hide emotions.

634
00:42:48.002 --> 00:42:50.867
We are susceptible to envy,

635
00:42:50.867 --> 00:42:53.379
we flee when they discover us

636
00:42:53.379 --> 00:42:56.771
and we don't know how to apologize.

637
00:42:57.500 --> 00:42:59.273
Am I wrong?

638
00:43:15.935 --> 00:43:18.325
<i>Every time we see each other,</i>

639
00:43:18.325 --> 00:43:21.829
<i>I feel like we are very similar, don't you?</i>

640
00:43:33.744 --> 00:43:35.977
Similar? Please.

641
00:43:46.223 --> 00:43:48.759
They finally arrived. It was a difficult trip, wasn't it?

642
00:43:48.759 --> 00:43:51.059
Thanks for visiting us.

643
00:43:51.059 --> 00:43:52.941
And... how are they?

644
00:43:52.941 --> 00:43:54.262
Thanks for coming.

645
00:43:54.262 --> 00:43:56.255
Hello!

646
00:43:56.255 --> 00:43:58.066
The truth,

647
00:43:58.066 --> 00:44:00.235
You went from being a boss to being a lazy person,

648
00:44:00.235 --> 00:44:01.901
and now you run the company.

649
00:44:01.901 --> 00:44:04.299
Your life is a roller coaster.

650
00:44:04.299 --> 00:44:05.600
Congratulations.

651
00:44:05.600 --> 00:44:08.819
You shouldn't have brought anything. What is all that?

652
00:44:08.819 --> 00:44:10.545
Surprise!

653
00:44:10.545 --> 00:44:13.640
I told you to take the tag off!

654
00:44:13.640 --> 00:44:16.084
"Camp Bom, triumph!"

655
00:44:16.084 --> 00:44:17.579
Thank you so much.

656
00:44:17.579 --> 00:44:19.520
Well, let's go.

657
00:44:22.459 --> 00:44:24.228
Be careful with your fingers.

658
00:44:24.228 --> 00:44:25.993
Please go ahead.

659
00:44:26.497 --> 00:44:29.063
The air is very pure here.

660
00:44:29.731 --> 00:44:32.300
- This tastes amazing.
- Is it tasty?

661
00:44:32.300 --> 00:44:33.234
Please help yourself to more.

662
00:44:33.234 --> 00:44:34.471
Thank you.

663
00:44:34.471 --> 00:44:35.940
You eat too.

664
00:44:35.940 --> 00:44:37.271
OK.

665
00:44:42.367 --> 00:44:43.744
Health!

666
00:44:47.181 --> 00:44:48.416
Are you happy?

667
00:44:48.416 --> 00:44:50.785
Yes, I love it.

668
00:44:52.456 --> 00:44:55.567
- Don't give it to me with your fingers!
- Try this.

669
00:44:55.567 --> 00:44:58.200
I serve myself.

670
00:44:58.200 --> 00:45:00.394
- How disgusting!
- Try it.

671
00:45:14.378 --> 00:45:15.976
What do you think about?

672
00:45:18.882 --> 00:45:20.362
Well...

673
00:45:21.352 --> 00:45:23.553
I find it incredible.

674
00:45:24.667 --> 00:45:27.954
We were strangers,
However, we find ourselves,

675
00:45:28.923 --> 00:45:31.095
we survived everything that happened

676
00:45:31.095 --> 00:45:34.428
and we ended up here together.

677
00:45:39.467 --> 00:45:40.801
It's true.

678
00:45:44.233 --> 00:45:45.573
If that day

679
00:45:46.240 --> 00:45:49.110
You wouldn't have made that brave confession,

680
00:45:50.834 --> 00:45:52.480
maybe...

681
00:45:54.973 --> 00:45:57.151
We wouldn't be sitting here now, would we?

682
00:45:59.460 --> 00:46:01.849
Did I make a confession?

683
00:46:03.294 --> 00:46:05.259
Look at you, you act like you have amnesia.

684
00:46:06.394 --> 00:46:09.363
Don't you remember what you said

685
00:46:10.071 --> 00:46:13.768
When did you ring the doorbell that day?

686
00:46:14.802 --> 00:46:16.471
What did I say exactly?

687
00:46:16.471 --> 00:46:19.055
I'm sure it wasn't a confession.

688
00:46:19.055 --> 00:46:20.474
It just can't be.

689
00:46:21.611 --> 00:46:23.511
You really don't remember.

690
00:46:23.511 --> 00:46:26.981
I, however, remember everything,

691
00:46:26.981 --> 00:46:30.387
even clothes and shoes
that you were wearing.

692
00:46:30.387 --> 00:46:32.219
It just can't be.

693
00:46:34.769 --> 00:46:37.992
You were wearing a white shirt
with a huge neck, they looked like wings,

694
00:46:37.992 --> 00:46:40.267
and white pants.

695
00:46:40.267 --> 00:46:41.796
And you had to hurry,

696
00:46:41.796 --> 00:46:44.233
you came almost running to my door

697
00:46:44.233 --> 00:46:46.111
in slippers.

698
00:46:46.111 --> 00:46:48.211
You looked like a cherub.

699
00:46:48.211 --> 00:46:50.738
How crazy!

700
00:46:52.863 --> 00:46:56.823
Is there something about you that I don't know?

701
00:46:56.823 --> 00:46:59.267
I watch you,

702
00:46:59.267 --> 00:47:01.048
I analyze you

703
00:47:01.901 --> 00:47:03.450
and I study you daily.

704
00:47:04.152 --> 00:47:06.187
I am an expert

705
00:47:06.187 --> 00:47:08.055
in Seo Jun Kyung.

706
00:47:08.523 --> 00:47:10.827
So you know everything about me.

707
00:47:15.463 --> 00:47:17.264
What's happening?

708
00:47:19.367 --> 00:47:20.535
I'm all day

709
00:47:20.535 --> 00:47:22.935
sitting at a desk.

710
00:47:22.935 --> 00:47:25.001
- I don't give more.
- Does your back hurt?

711
00:47:25.001 --> 00:47:26.808
There.

712
00:47:26.808 --> 00:47:27.656
Here?

713
00:47:27.656 --> 00:47:28.576
Right there.

714
00:47:28.576 --> 00:47:32.016
Shouldn't it hurt more when I press like that?

715
00:47:32.016 --> 00:47:34.315
- I love it.
- Does it hurt even more?

716
00:47:34.315 --> 00:47:38.419
I thought I'd have a housewarming party

717
00:47:38.419 --> 00:47:42.356
It was something that everyone did,
but it is not like that.

718
00:47:43.608 --> 00:47:45.359
What are you saying?

719
00:47:46.273 --> 00:47:50.968
It feels like it's showing
that's going well for me,

720
00:47:50.968 --> 00:47:55.336
or promising myself
that I will live better from now on.

721
00:47:56.113 --> 00:47:58.334
Although I don't know well

722
00:47:58.334 --> 00:48:00.241
What does it mean to "live well."

723
00:48:01.113 --> 00:48:04.078
Living well means...

724
00:48:05.480 --> 00:48:07.715
put on a towel

725
00:48:07.715 --> 00:48:11.085
in the face

726
00:48:11.085 --> 00:48:13.454
when it's soft and fluffy,

727
00:48:13.454 --> 00:48:16.500
then on the feet

728
00:48:16.500 --> 00:48:19.126
when it frays and scratches you.

729
00:48:19.654 --> 00:48:24.164
And when it's stained and stretched,
even after boiling it,

730
00:48:24.634 --> 00:48:27.234
use it as a rag.

731
00:48:29.470 --> 00:48:31.872
live like this

732
00:48:32.607 --> 00:48:35.376
is to live well.

733
00:48:39.001 --> 00:48:41.382
Thanks for coming.

734
00:48:43.687 --> 00:48:45.653
I'm serious.

735
00:48:49.793 --> 00:48:51.558
Ja Yeong.

736
00:49:16.053 --> 00:49:19.053
<i>♪ Let's enjoy life ♪</i>

737
00:49:19.053 --> 00:49:22.253
<i>♪ Let's enjoy life ♪</i>

738
00:49:22.253 --> 00:49:24.795
<i>♪ Let's try it ♪</i>

739
00:49:24.795 --> 00:49:27.328
<i>♪ Let's enjoy life ♪</i>

740
00:49:28.766 --> 00:49:31.332
<i>♪ Let's enjoy life ♪</i>

741
00:49:31.332 --> 00:49:33.337
<i>♪ Let's enjoy life ♪</i>

742
00:49:33.337 --> 00:49:35.803
She is drunk.

743
00:49:37.338 --> 00:49:39.506
And no one forced her to drink.

744
00:49:56.324 --> 00:49:57.992
Wait.

745
00:49:57.992 --> 00:50:00.068
That...?

746
00:50:00.068 --> 00:50:00.965
What are you doing?

747
00:50:00.965 --> 00:50:02.652
I wanted to know what it feels like.

748
00:50:02.652 --> 00:50:03.864
What does it feel like?

749
00:50:06.367 --> 00:50:07.271
That?

750
00:50:07.271 --> 00:50:09.069
Come home early, darling.

751
00:50:11.175 --> 00:50:12.712
Come on.

752
00:50:12.712 --> 00:50:15.509
We look like newlyweds.

753
00:50:16.480 --> 00:50:18.515
This suit is old.

754
00:50:18.515 --> 00:50:20.381
Is it the only one you have?

755
00:50:21.185 --> 00:50:24.218
Why would I have others?

756
00:50:24.729 --> 00:50:27.358
That shows
the life I have led until now.

757
00:50:27.358 --> 00:50:29.601
When you have the prize money,

758
00:50:29.601 --> 00:50:31.534
I'll buy you a tie.

759
00:50:31.534 --> 00:50:32.760
No,

760
00:50:33.427 --> 00:50:35.090
a complete suit,

761
00:50:35.090 --> 00:50:36.634
a sophisticated one.

762
00:50:36.634 --> 00:50:40.200
You are already spending money you don't earn yet.

763
00:50:41.405 --> 00:50:43.334
When I am a novelist

764
00:50:43.334 --> 00:50:45.734
and you are a teacher,

765
00:50:45.734 --> 00:50:47.678
shall we get married?

766
00:50:47.678 --> 00:50:49.710
That? You make me blush.

767
00:50:49.710 --> 00:50:51.148
Enough.

768
00:50:51.148 --> 00:50:53.717
Finish them!

769
00:50:53.717 --> 00:50:54.551
Yes.

770
00:50:54.551 --> 00:50:56.350
- I won't let you down.
- Yes.

771
00:50:57.618 --> 00:50:59.453
- I'll be in touch.
- Yes.

772
00:50:59.453 --> 00:51:01.722
- Cheer up!
- Yes.

773
00:51:04.025 --> 00:51:07.198
The teacher left everything ready,
don't worry.

774
00:51:07.198 --> 00:51:10.044
<i>Don't panic.</i>

775
00:51:10.044 --> 00:51:12.433
<i>Answer "Yes! Yes!" to what they ask you.</i>

776
00:51:12.433 --> 00:51:13.705
Panic? Please...

777
00:51:13.705 --> 00:51:15.039
Okay, good luck.

778
00:51:15.039 --> 00:51:16.904
You will do well, don't be nervous.

779
00:51:16.904 --> 00:51:18.542
<i>I told you I'm not nervous.</i>

780
00:51:18.542 --> 00:51:19.773
It's okay.

781
00:51:21.111 --> 00:51:23.410
For me, it's nervous.

782
00:51:40.428 --> 00:51:42.185
Jin Ho!

783
00:51:42.185 --> 00:51:44.098
Jin Ho, look at this.

784
00:51:44.098 --> 00:51:47.157
There are many aralia shoots there.

785
00:51:47.157 --> 00:51:48.735
Look.

786
00:51:53.210 --> 00:51:54.608
No.

787
00:51:55.946 --> 00:51:58.011
My God, what's wrong with me?

788
00:52:05.823 --> 00:52:07.637
You did an internship at a radio station.

789
00:52:07.637 --> 00:52:10.367
- That's how it is.
- You passed the thesis.

790
00:52:10.367 --> 00:52:11.558
Yes.

791
00:52:13.027 --> 00:52:15.498
Are you graduating with six credits this semester?

792
00:52:15.498 --> 00:52:17.357
Yes that's how it is.

793
00:52:17.357 --> 00:52:20.267
Why is your average average?

794
00:52:21.368 --> 00:52:22.836
Well...

795
00:52:23.370 --> 00:52:27.658
I had some personal issues.

796
00:52:27.658 --> 00:52:29.057
What matters?

797
00:52:29.057 --> 00:52:30.511
Well...

798
00:52:31.581 --> 00:52:33.380
It's okay, it doesn't matter.

799
00:52:33.380 --> 00:52:34.849
Good.

800
00:52:34.849 --> 00:52:37.518
Professor Song recommended you,

801
00:52:37.518 --> 00:52:39.990
and we have a free position for Humanities,

802
00:52:39.990 --> 00:52:42.735
so you wouldn't be a bad candidate
for the position.

803
00:52:42.735 --> 00:52:44.225
But there is a protocol.

804
00:52:44.225 --> 00:52:47.298
I will talk to the head of the department
and I will contact you soon.

805
00:52:47.298 --> 00:52:48.632
Very good.

806
00:52:48.632 --> 00:52:50.164
Thank you.

807
00:52:54.726 --> 00:52:56.303
Jin Ho,

808
00:52:57.001 --> 00:52:58.972
are you still angry?

809
00:53:00.407 --> 00:53:01.568
It's not about being angry.

810
00:53:01.568 --> 00:53:05.082
A fire in these mountains
it would be a disaster.

811
00:53:05.082 --> 00:53:07.814
You're right, it could have been terrible.

812
00:53:08.749 --> 00:53:11.016
I became overly relaxed when I moved here.

813
00:53:11.016 --> 00:53:12.686
I disconnected.

814
00:53:13.361 --> 00:53:15.159
Very sorry.

815
00:53:15.159 --> 00:53:18.258
I promise I'll pay more attention.
from now on.

816
00:53:20.181 --> 00:53:22.055
I'm lucky you're so happy here.

817
00:53:22.055 --> 00:53:25.165
to do those crazy things.

818
00:53:27.504 --> 00:53:30.637
Does that mean you're not angry anymore?

819
00:53:31.575 --> 00:53:33.473
No, I still hold a grudge against you.

820
00:53:34.403 --> 00:53:35.302
Don't be like that.

821
00:53:35.302 --> 00:53:37.044
Enough.

822
00:53:40.091 --> 00:53:41.372
Don't tickle me.

823
00:53:41.372 --> 00:53:43.387
I'm not over it, so leave.

824
00:53:43.387 --> 00:53:44.785
Enough.

825
00:53:45.823 --> 00:53:47.254
No.

826
00:53:49.456 --> 00:53:53.560
Do you know what matters more than the diamond
in a marriage proposal?

827
00:53:54.398 --> 00:53:55.796
That?

828
00:53:56.333 --> 00:53:57.764
The right time.

829
00:53:58.391 --> 00:54:00.234
Does it seem cliché to you?

830
00:54:00.234 --> 00:54:04.038
It does not depend on your moment or that of the couple.

831
00:54:04.038 --> 00:54:06.673
It has to be a moment
that belongs only to her.

832
00:54:07.563 --> 00:54:09.780
But how to predict that moment

833
00:54:09.780 --> 00:54:11.545
It's the most difficult.

834
00:54:19.156 --> 00:54:21.892
I told you I could take
the academy bus.

835
00:54:21.892 --> 00:54:23.661
I have nothing else to do.

836
00:54:23.661 --> 00:54:25.459
I don't have a job.

837
00:54:27.097 --> 00:54:28.465
So, go look for a job.

838
00:54:28.465 --> 00:54:32.299
What if you miss class?
and are we going to eat <i>tteokbokki</i>?

839
00:54:33.300 --> 00:54:36.471
Why don't you leave the academy?
and you stay with me?

840
00:54:36.471 --> 00:54:39.239
How am I going to give up?

841
00:54:39.874 --> 00:54:41.620
You are not...

842
00:54:41.620 --> 00:54:43.690
like other moms.

843
00:54:43.690 --> 00:54:47.214
Would you like me to be like them?

844
00:54:47.918 --> 00:54:49.420
No,

845
00:54:49.420 --> 00:54:50.593
I would hate it.

846
00:54:53.434 --> 00:54:54.788
And...

847
00:54:56.402 --> 00:54:58.492
Aren't you going out with anyone?

848
00:54:59.630 --> 00:55:00.927
Why do you ask me?

849
00:55:02.390 --> 00:55:03.897
Just...

850
00:55:05.057 --> 00:55:06.670
I say it

851
00:55:06.670 --> 00:55:09.017
because dad has a girlfriend.

852
00:55:09.017 --> 00:55:11.537
You didn't like the idea
to go out with someone.

853
00:55:11.537 --> 00:55:13.614
You wanted the three of them,

854
00:55:13.614 --> 00:55:16.810
You, dad and I, lived together.

855
00:55:17.311 --> 00:55:18.578
That was before.

856
00:55:18.578 --> 00:55:20.384
I have already matured.

857
00:55:20.384 --> 00:55:21.815
And now?

858
00:55:22.453 --> 00:55:25.285
Do you want me to go out with someone?

859
00:55:26.553 --> 00:55:28.155
I don't want...

860
00:55:30.167 --> 00:55:32.426
that you are alone

861
00:55:35.366 --> 00:55:37.331
Do I look lonely?

862
00:55:40.467 --> 00:55:41.768
Well...

863
00:55:43.274 --> 00:55:44.771
maybe a little.

864
00:55:48.479 --> 00:55:49.643
Alright.

865
00:55:49.643 --> 00:55:52.079
I will strive not to be alone.

866
00:55:55.312 --> 00:55:57.029
I'm in a bind.

867
00:55:57.029 --> 00:55:59.368
The recording does not progress,

868
00:55:59.368 --> 00:56:00.875
I think it will take quite some time.

869
00:56:00.875 --> 00:56:02.155
Oh really?

870
00:56:02.155 --> 00:56:04.424
I was making curry.

871
00:56:05.790 --> 00:56:08.128
I'm exhausted today.

872
00:56:09.133 --> 00:56:11.398
The person I love is making curry.

873
00:56:11.966 --> 00:56:13.663
Today was the perfect day for that.

874
00:56:15.035 --> 00:56:17.204
I guess it's not the time.

875
00:56:36.083 --> 00:56:37.370
It's him!

876
00:56:43.567 --> 00:56:44.698
Hi teacher.

877
00:56:44.698 --> 00:56:47.267
<i>Everything is fixed.</i>

878
00:56:47.267 --> 00:56:49.273
<i>You will be in charge of the class
of the next semester.</i>

879
00:56:49.273 --> 00:56:50.970
Really?

880
00:56:50.970 --> 00:56:53.574
<i>Let's try a semester.</i>

881
00:56:53.574 --> 00:56:55.713
<i>If the kids like it, you will continue.</i>

882
00:56:55.713 --> 00:56:57.477
Thank you very much.

883
00:56:58.110 --> 00:57:00.114
<i>- And one more thing.</i>
- Yes.

884
00:57:00.114 --> 00:57:02.249
<i>You must have five million ready.</i>

885
00:57:04.635 --> 00:57:05.935
Excuse me?

886
00:57:06.420 --> 00:57:10.324
<i>Many teachers are interested
in those general elective subjects,</i>

887
00:57:10.324 --> 00:57:12.133
<i>and the complaints are endless.</i>

888
00:57:12.133 --> 00:57:14.200
<i>As long as you have that sum, you will be fine.</i>

889
00:57:14.200 --> 00:57:16.029
<i>Su Jin said</i>

890
00:57:17.197 --> 00:57:19.334
<i>this spring feels bitter.</i>

891
00:57:19.334 --> 00:57:21.167
Sure.

892
00:57:21.167 --> 00:57:22.334
<i>Very cruel.</i>

893
00:57:22.334 --> 00:57:24.237
When do I have to have it ready?

894
00:57:25.472 --> 00:57:29.242
<i>Now that I think about it,
We have a wrong idea about spring.</i>

895
00:57:30.577 --> 00:57:32.813
<i>The sun is warm,</i>

896
00:57:34.133 --> 00:57:38.251
<i>neither too intense nor too soft,
It seems like a nice season.</i>

897
00:57:39.553 --> 00:57:43.223
<i>He is kind and makes us lower our guard,</i>

898
00:57:45.459 --> 00:57:48.862
<i>but spring is not so kind.</i>

899
00:57:50.330 --> 00:57:51.350
Thank you very much.

900
00:57:51.350 --> 00:57:52.511
You're welcome, rest.

901
00:57:52.511 --> 00:57:53.970
Thank you.

902
00:57:53.970 --> 00:57:55.435
Bye bye.

903
00:57:56.473 --> 00:57:59.376
<i>I thought only warmer days would come.</i>

904
00:57:59.376 --> 00:58:00.390
Hello, Ja Yeong.

905
00:58:00.390 --> 00:58:02.970
<i>Have you seen our Bom?</i>

906
00:58:02.970 --> 00:58:07.781
<i>But sometimes
an unexpected cold wave surprises us.</i>

907
00:58:07.781 --> 00:58:10.217
I don't see Bom anywhere.

908
00:58:11.570 --> 00:58:13.119
Boom!

909
00:58:14.058 --> 00:58:16.122
Boom, where are you?

910
00:58:17.600 --> 00:58:21.595
<i>The unstable air
creates large temperature changes.</i>

911
00:58:25.098 --> 00:58:27.968
<i>The differences between day and night</i>

912
00:58:29.601 --> 00:58:32.772
<i>they catch us off guard.</i>

913
00:58:34.761 --> 00:58:37.911
<i>It confuses us in a fog</i>

914
00:58:39.701 --> 00:58:42.716
<i>colorless but shiny.</i>

915
00:58:44.751 --> 00:58:46.319
<i>Spring...</i>

916
00:58:48.001 --> 00:58:49.923
<i>happens again this year,</i>

917
00:58:51.734 --> 00:58:53.760
<i>and leaves us...</i>

918
00:58:55.968 --> 00:58:57.964
<i>far from any sense of security.</i>

